claudeqt (0.0.1-0qt6~ppa1~noble1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Initial source package. Ships three binary packages —
    claudeqt (GUI), claudeqt-remote (headless daemon),
    claudeqt-common (arch:all shared data) — built against the KF5
    syntax-highlighting Qt6 backport shipped in the same PPA
    (kf5syntaxhighlighting-qt6).
  * claudeqt is the full desktop skeleton: project/session tree
    with drag-and-drop and sort-order modes, tabbed code editor
    with KSyntaxHighlighting, auto-growing chat input with draft
    persistence, settings dialog, dark theme, leader-elected IPC
    hub for multi-window sync. Claude CLI wire integration is not
    yet included; chat drafts persist locally but are not sent.
  * claudeqt-remote is a signalfd+timerfd+sd_notify watchdog stub:
    Type=notify, WatchdogSec=30, 10 s WATCHDOG=1 cadence. The full
    JSON-RPC/TLS daemon will be added in a future release; the
    stub is shipped now so the service contract and systemd
    integration are in place.
  * debian/rules uses dh-cmake with cmake+ninja buildsystem and
    -DCLAUDEQT_SYSTEM_INTEGRATION=ON -DBUILD_TESTING=OFF.
  * claudeqt-remote postinst creates the dedicated system user
    `claudeqt` (home /var/lib/claudeqt, shell /usr/sbin/nologin),
    generates a self-signed Ed25519 TLS cert under
    /etc/claudeqt/certs, and prints state-aware NEXT STEPS hints.
  * claudeqt-remote unit defaults to IPAddressDeny=any +
    IPAddressAllow=localhost; admins extend via drop-in files in
    /etc/systemd/system/claudeqt-remote.service.d/ (additive merge
    of IPAddressAllow= across drop-ins).
  * Noble-only for this upload; Resolute upload will follow when
    the port is validated. Version suffix `-0qt6~ppa1~noble1`
    keeps the `qt6` marker (explicit signal that this is the Qt6
    build path) and follows the `~ppa<N>~<distro>N` convention for
    PPA revisions scoped to a specific Ubuntu series.

 -- Aaron Yourk <ayourk@gmail.com>  Mon, 13 Apr 2026 22:00:00 -0400
